1.2 Sampling of data to 2%

Reduced data to such low level for faster implementation of ML algos

set.seed(2020)

credit_card_samp <- credit_card %>% 
                      dplyr::sample_frac(0.02)


print(prop.table(table(credit_card_samp$Class)) * 100)

        0         1 
99.806882  0.193118 
print(table(credit_card_samp$Class))

   0    1 
5685   11

1.3 Data PreProcessing

1.3.1 Data Normalization / Scaling

Since this data is already scaled by using PCA so we will not do any scaling

1.4 Train Test Split

split_train_index <- createDataPartition(y = credit_card_samp$Class, p = 0.70, list = F)

train <- credit_card_samp[split_train_index, ]
test <- credit_card_samp[-split_train_index, ]
print(dim(train))
[1] 3988   31
print(dim(test))
[1] 1708   31

1.5 Model Building

1.5.1 metric & test options setting

control <- trainControl(method="repeatedcv", number = 5, repeats = 3, verboseIter = T)
seed <- 7

1.5.2 Type of Models

`Linear methods`: Linear Discriminant Analysis and Logistic Regression.
`Non-Linear methods`: Neural Network, SVM, kNN and Naive Bayes
`Trees and Rules`: CART, J48 and PART
`Ensembles of Trees`: C5.0, Bagged CART, Random Forest and Stochastic Gradient Boosting
